The implementation of the std random number engines is not defined by the standard and might vary from library to library. In fact, running that code from inside Unreal Engine produces 145 as first value
```
std::minstd_rand Engine;
Engine.seed(123456789);
UE_LOG(LogCarla, Error, TEXT("First random number is %d"), std::uniform_int_distribution<int32>(0, 151)(Engine));
```

Unreal is compiled using libc++ (instead of libstdc++ that Linux usually uses), you might try linking against libc++ in your external program and it might produce the same results.
